Color of axis label is set to be [axisLine.lineStyle.color](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#singleAxis.axisLine.lineStyle.color) by default. Callback function is supported, in the following format:

```js
(val: string) => Color
```

Parameter is the text of label, and return value is the color. See the following example:

```js
textStyle: {
color: function (value, index) {
return value >= 0 ? 'green' : 'red';
}
}
```

The color of the splitLine, which could be set separately.

SplitLine color could also be set in color array, which the split lines would take as their colors in turns.

Example:
```
splitLine: {
lineStyle: {
// Dark and light colors will be used in turns
color: ['#aaa', '#ddd']
}
}
```

desc:
Category data, available in [type](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#singleAxis.type): 'category' axis.

If [type](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#singleAxis.type) is not specified, but `axis.data` is specified, the [type](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#singleAxis.type) is auto set as `'category'`.

If [type](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#singleAxis.type) is specified as `'category'`, but `axis.data` is not specified, `axis.data` will be auto collected from [series.data](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#series.data). It brings convenience, but we should notice that `axis.data` provides then value range of the `'category'` axis. If  it is auto collected from [series.data](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#series.data), Only the values appearing in [series.data](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#series.data) can be collected. For example, if [series.data](https://echarts.apache.org/en/option.html#series.data) is empty, nothing will be collected.


Example:

```js
// Name list of all categories
data: ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']
// Each item could also be a specific configuration item.
// In this case, `value` is used as the category name.
data: [{
value: 'Monday',
// Highlight Monday
textStyle: {
fontSize: 20,
color: 'red'
}
}, 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']
```

